http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/House-gutted-near-Vanchiyoor/article14004437.ece

A house was gutted in an early morning fire accident near Vanchiyoor here on Sunday.According to Fire and Rescue Services personnel, the house, one with a thatched roof, had caught fire around 1 a.m. in Chirakkulam Colony, reportedly due to a short circuit. The three occupants – Rajiv, his wife Manju and her father – managed to escape to safety and there were no casualties reported. Two fire engines from the Chengalchoola Fire Station doused the fire, which is estimated to have caused damage worth over Rs.1 lakh .